-- Ukraine Intends to Export Sugar to Bangladesh, Minister Says
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-03-13T15:49:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-13/ukraine-intends-to-export-sugar-to-bangladesh-minister-says.html
Ukraine intends to export sugar to
 Bangladesh , according to Mykola Prysyazhnyuk, Ukraine’s
agriculture minister.  “This is a new and promising market,” Prysyazhnyuk told
reporters today in Kiev. “We know that we can supply grains to
Bangladesh and, most important, we can have a market there for
our sugar,” the minister said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  